      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Good",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "For ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Harvest Moon/Story of Seasons",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " newbies, especially younger kids, this sweet and innocent remake acts as a wonderful introduction to the series. They can experience many attractive features without toiling for hours to unlock them. Although it’s been a looong time since I played the first ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A Wonderful Life",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " – and I have forgotten virtually everything about it – I just don’t remember the oldest-school ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Harvest Moon",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " games being so effortless and fast-paced. I played the ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "SNES original",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://harvest-moon.fandom.com/wiki/Harvest_Moon_(SNES)",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "; that’s how old I am.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "For instance, your dad’s buddy, old man Takakura, literally lives on your property and has your back from day one. He keeps providing you with animals, tools, advice, and so on, so your life is less challenging. Rather than run around to different establishments, you order animals, breeding, feed, and facilities via your farm’s ledger, and Takakura takes care of the rest. He even feeds your pooch!",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Other stuff, for example, that makes it easier: your beginner’s bag has 48 slots, each milking provides multiple milk bottles, your scattered chicken feed lasts ages, and the Harvest Sprites present you with the elusive Blue Feather. And where are those boulder-riddled fields that we had to upgrade our hammers to smash in previous titles? And your house magically expands itself, so you don’t have to painstakingly accumulate the resources to do so. And so on.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "About the “fast-paced” comment, most ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Harvest Moon",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "/",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Story of Seasons",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " games have 30-day seasons. But the remake has replaced them with 10-day seasons. They go by super fast. Maybe the creators thought the lengthier seasons might become monotonous over the long haul, given the generational focus. In any case, like its seasons, the plot moves pretty quickly, which may be good for younger kids who might have shorter attention spans.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "What about us old(er) folk who played the original? ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A Wonderful Life",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " offers a few modernisations. You can customise your protagonist’s skin and eye colours. You can be non-binary and gay. If you get bored with your hairdo and clothes, you may switch them. The developers have also added to the cast some much-needed ethnic diversity.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I think you need to propose by the end of Year 1. Then each gameplay year, the game skips ahead a few years so you see your sweet little bub grow. Aww. They have likes and abilities that develop over time, being: ranching, farming, athletics, music, art, and academics.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Probably, the bestest part for me was raising my adorable animals. A",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": " ",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              },
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 2,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Harvestella",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "__GHOST_URL__/harvestella-switch-review",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " criticism of mine was that the game lacked enough cutesy animal interactivity. So, I loved how ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A Wonderful Life",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " lets you literally ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "snuggle",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " every pet/inedible livestock creature. And all the rest, like brushing, shearing, training (dog), milking, breeding, etc., with the charming reactions. The pink sheep are back! Provide lots of affection and you are rewarded with better quality products. And your unique cow variants (Normal, Brown, Marble, and Star) produce distinctive milk, selling at different prices.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Although Forgotten Valley is quite small, there’s the usual beach, forest, and town. Instead of a bottomless mine, the valley has an archaeological dig site where you may chance upon some rare artefacts to sell to Van, the wandering merchant. Lastly, calming music and nice sound effects.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "TL;DR",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "Lovely, wholesome game; good and easy entry point, especially for kids",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
